00:15:40.640 --> 00:15:41.560
"Futaba: Age 15"

00:15:41.560 --> 00:15:43.060
"Futaba: Age 15"
Wha...?!

00:15:43.060 --> 00:15:45.610
You want to live alone in Tokyo?

00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:46.400
Yeah...

00:15:46.400 --> 00:15:50.150
"School Prospectus"

00:15:46.400 --> 00:15:50.150
I want to try living on my own.

00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:57.040
I don't think it's good for me to be
dependent on you forever, Grandpa.

00:15:58.240 --> 00:15:59.750
I understand.

00:16:01.330 --> 00:16:03.250
You look so grim!

00:16:03.250 --> 00:16:05.670
Huh? You sure it's okay?

00:16:05.670 --> 00:16:10.630
Futaba, I know you. You made up your mind
after giving it a lot of thought, right?

00:16:10.630 --> 00:16:16.640
Well, you know what they say: "If you
love your child, send her on a journey."

00:16:17.850 --> 00:16:19.310
Th-Thanks!

00:16:19.310 --> 00:16:21.270
However!

00:16:21.270 --> 00:16:27.190
Beware of those city boys.
They're wolves, the whole lot of them.

00:16:27.190 --> 00:16:29.530
A-All right...

00:16:31.700 --> 00:16:35.120
I'm more or less done unpacking...

00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:37.870
Tomorrow's the first day of school.

00:16:37.870 --> 00:16:43.620
I wonder if I'll make any friends.
Well, I've got to try....

00:16:43.620 --> 00:16:46.330
Oh. So...

00:16:46.330 --> 00:16:51.800
...she's been living on her own since
then. That's why she's such a good cook.

00:16:51.800 --> 00:16:56.640
What? Don't tell me you've had
some of Futaba's home cooking.

00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:58.970
I have, and it was really good.

00:16:58.970 --> 00:17:02.560
Whaaaaat?!

00:17:06.150 --> 00:17:09.320
You're such a good cook, Futaba.

00:17:11.070 --> 00:17:15.200
So, what did you make that fellow?

00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:18.620
Enough is enough! You come
and spend the night uninvited.

00:17:18.620 --> 00:17:22.500
You go head-to-head with Takeda-<i>senpai</i>.
Knock it off, okay?

00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:24.910
I'm worried about you, Futaba.

00:17:24.910 --> 00:17:27.830
I'm 23, you know!

00:17:27.830 --> 00:17:30.920
It's doesn't matter how old you are.
I still worry about you.

00:17:34.260 --> 00:17:38.430
Oh, how lovely!
Is this your White Day gift?

00:17:38.430 --> 00:17:43.730
I just love macarons. Thanks!

00:17:43.730 --> 00:17:45.440
I'm glad to hear that.

00:17:45.440 --> 00:17:50.400
Sakurai-<i>san </i>loves macarons.
Better make a note of that...

00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:53.740
I doubt that note will ever get any use.

00:17:53.740 --> 00:17:54.740
Hey.

00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:56.780
You seen Igarashi around?

00:17:56.780 --> 00:18:01.120
Oh, Igarashi-<i>chan</i>? I think she's...

00:18:03.080 --> 00:18:05.330
Oh, there you are.

00:18:05.330 --> 00:18:07.710
Igarashi...

00:18:07.710 --> 00:18:10.960
Oh, Senpai...

00:18:11.960 --> 00:18:13.590
Uhhh...

00:18:16.130 --> 00:18:20.350
There sure is a lot of
pollen flying around.

00:18:20.350 --> 00:18:23.640
Here, I went and got you a variety
of stuff from the drug store.

00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:26.350
Thank you...

00:18:26.350 --> 00:18:29.520
Open your eyes.
I'm putting the drops in now.

00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:37.360
That got rid of some of the discomfort...
Sorry about that.

00:18:37.360 --> 00:18:41.870
That's okay. But you should at least learn
how to put drops in your own eyes.

00:18:41.870 --> 00:18:45.000
I don't know why, but the tip
of the eye dropper scares me.

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:47.290
Sounds like you've got a sore throat, too.

00:18:47.290 --> 00:18:48.870
Have some hard candy.

00:18:48.870 --> 00:18:50.920
Thank you.

00:18:54.340 --> 00:18:56.170
Okay, I'm heading back to my desk.

00:18:56.170 --> 00:18:58.010
All right.

00:18:58.010 --> 00:19:00.970
Since you shared that chocolate
with me a while back...

00:19:00.970 --> 00:19:04.010
